exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Get into a high plank position. Place your hands firmly on the ground, directly under shoulders. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Push your body up, back to the initial position. Repeat.

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
exercises.description: Sit on the edge of a chair or bench with your hands next to your thighs. Lift your body out in front of the bench with your knees slightly bent, and lower your body by bending at the elbows until you reach about a 90-degree angle. Push your body up, back to the initial position. Repeat.

exercises.name: Plank Up-Downs
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Lower one arm to bring the elbow and forearm to the floor. Do the same with the other arm. Then push back up onto your hands one arm at a time. Repeat.

exercises.name: Inchworms
exercises.description: Stand straight. Bend over and touch the floor with your hands, keeping your legs straight. Walk your hands forward until you reach a high plank position. Walk your hands back toward your feet and stand up. Repeat.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Place your hands shoulder-width apart. Keeping your back straight, lower your body until your chest almost touches the floor.

exercises.name: Diamond push-ups
exercises.description: Bring your hands close together in a diamond shape. Lower your body until your chest almost touches your hands.

exercises.name: Dips
exercises.description: Hold onto a set of parallel bars and lower your body until your elbows are at a 90-degree angle. Push back up.

exercises.name: Chin-ups
exercises.description: Hang from a bar with an underhand grip, palms facing towards you. Pull yourself up until your chin is over the bar.

exercises.name: Pull-ups
exercises.description: Hang from a bar with an overhand grip, palms facing away from you. Pull yourself up until your chin is over the bar.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Push-ups
exercises.description: Place the medicine ball under one hand, perform a push-up, roll the ball to your other hand and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Bicep Curls
exercises.description: Stand up with your torso upright while holding a barbell at a shoulder-width grip. Curl the weights while contracting your biceps as you breathe out.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Tricep Dips
exercises.description: Sit on the medicine ball with your hands supporting you at either side. Lower your body by bending your elbows until your arms are at about a 90-degree angle, then push back up.

exercises.name: Barbell Overhead Press
exercises.description: Stand with the bar on your front shoulders, and your hands next to your shoulders. Press the bar over your head, until it’s balanced over your shoulders and mid-foot. Lock your elbows at the top.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Hammer Curls
exercises.description: Hold the medicine ball in both hands, let it hang at arm's length straight down. Bend your elbows and curl as high as you can. Lower the medicine ball back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Skullcrushers
exercises.description: Lie back on a flat bench with a barbell. Lower the bar towards your forehead by bending your elbows. Keep your upper arms still, only moving your forearms.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Tricep Extension
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a medicine ball with both hands. Extend your arms overhead, then bend your elbows to lower the ball behind your head. Extend your arms to return to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Reverse Curl
exercises.description: Hold a barbell with a shoulder-width grip, palms facing down. Keep your elbows close to your torso at all times. Curl the weights while contracting your biceps as you breathe out.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Curls
exercises.description: Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand. Keep the elbows close to the torso and make a curl. Then, return to the original position.

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
exercises.description: On a bench, place your hands shoulder-width apart. Extend your legs out in front of you. Lower your body towards the floor with your elbows at a 90-degree angle. Push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Swing
exercises.description: Stand up straight, with feet a bit wider than hip-distance apart. Grab the handle with both hands, keeping the palms face down and arms in front of the body. Maintain a slight bend to the knee and drive the hips back, lowering the body—but not too low. Then, in a fluid motion, explosively drive the hips forward while swinging the kettlebell, keeping the glutes and core engaged.

exercises.name: Barbell Bicep Curls
exercises.description: Stand up with your torso upright while holding a barbell at a shoulder-width grip. While holding the upper arms stationary, curl the weights forward while contracting the biceps as you breathe out. Continue the movement until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level.

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
exercises.description: Position your hands shoulder-width apart on a secured bench or stable chair. Move your bottom off the front of the bench with your legs extended out in front of you. Lower your body until your arms are at about a 90-degree angle then slowly push yourself back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Hammer Curls
exercises.description: Stand up with your torso upright and a dumbbell on each hand being held at arms length. The elbows should be close to the torso. While holding the upper arm stationary, curl the weights while contracting the biceps as you breathe out.

exercises.name: Overhead Tricep Extension
exercises.description: Stand up with a dumbbell held by both hands. Your feet should be about shoulder width apart from each other. Slowly use both hands to lift the dumbbell over your head until both arms are fully extended. The resistance should be resting in the palms of your hands with your thumbs around it.

exercises.name: Diamond Push-ups
exercises.description: Get into a push-up position with your hands close together under your chest. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Pause at the bottom, and then push yourself back to the starting position as quickly as possible.

exercises.name: Underhand Kickbacks
exercises.description: Stand up straight while holding a dumbbell with the right arm fully extended to the side and your left hand holding your waist. Your feet should be placed shoulder width apart. This will be your starting position. While keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the weight while contracting the biceps.

exercises.name: Preacher Curls
exercises.description: Hold a barbell with both hands, palms up and a few inches apart. The elbows should be close to the torso. The upper arms should be stationary and only the forearms should move. Breathe out as you curl the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted.

exercises.name: Skull Crushers
exercises.description: Lie down on a flat bench with a barbell in your hands. Lower the bar by using your elbows to flex until the bar is just about one inch from your forehead. Always keep your elbows in as you perform this movement.

exercises.name: Barbell Curl
exercises.description: Stand up with your torso upright while holding a barbell at a shoulder-width grip. Curl the weights while contracting your biceps as you breathe out. Continue the movement until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Skull Crusher
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench with a dumbbell on each hand held at arms length. Keep your elbows in and your arms perpendicular to the floor. Lower the weight until the dumbbells are near your ears. Contract your triceps to return to the starting position.

exercises.name: Hammer Curl
exercises.description: Stand up with your torso upright and a dumbbell on each hand being held at arms length. While keeping your upper arms stationary, curl the weights while contracting your biceps as you breathe out.

exercises.name: Tricep Kickback
exercises.description: Start with a dumbbell in each hand and your palms facing your torso. Keep your back straight with a slight bend in the knees and bend forward at the waist. Lift the dumbbells back and up while keeping your elbows close to your body.

exercises.name: Reverse Curl
exercises.description: Stand up with your torso upright while holding a barbell at a shoulder-width grip. The palm of your hands should be facing down (pronated grip). Curl the weights while contracting your biceps as you breathe out.

exercises.name: Overhead Tricep Extension
exercises.description: Stand up with a small barbell, grip it at shoulder width. Lift the barbell over your head until your arms are fully extended. Keep your elbows in and slowly lower the barbell behind your head as you hold the upper arms stationary.

exercises.name: Concentration Curl
exercises.description: Sit on the end of a flat bench with a dumbbell in your right arm, palm facing upward. Lean forward so that your right elbow is touching the inside of your right thigh. Curl the dumbbell towards your chest, keeping your elbow and thigh in contact.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Tricep Extension
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench holding a dumbbell in both hands. Your arms should be extended at a 90-degree angle from your torso and your palms should be facing in. Lower the weight until the dumbbell is near your forehead. Extend your arms to return to the starting position.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Swing
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, grab the handle with both hands, and sink into a squat. Drive your hips forward to swing the kettlebell up to shoulder height, then drop back down into the squat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Bicep Curl
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward, and keep your back straight and chest up. Without moving your upper arms, bend your elbows and curl the weights toward your shoulders. Slowly lower them back down, keeping control of the weight throughout the descent.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Tricep Extension
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand and lift them over your head, keeping your elbows close to your ears and your palms facing each other. Lower the dumbbells down by bending at the elbow, then push back up to the start.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Push your body up back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Pull-ups
exercises.description: Grab the bar with your palms facing outward. Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dips
exercises.description: Hold onto the parallel bars of a dip station and lower your body until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. Push back up to the start.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Place hands firmly on the ground, directly under shoulders. Lower your body until chest nearly touches the floor. Push your body up returning to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dips
exercises.description: Position your hands shoulder-width apart on a secured bench. Straighten out your arms and keep a little bend in your elbows in order to always keep tension on your triceps and off your elbow joints. Slowly lower your body down towards the floor until your arms are at about a 90-degree angle. Once you reach the bottom of the movement, press down into the bench to straighten your elbows, returning to the starting position.

exercises.name: Pull-ups
exercises.description: Grab the pull-up bar with your palms down (shoulder-width grip). Hang to the pull-up bar with straight arms and your legs off the floor. Pull yourself up by pulling your elbows down to the floor. Go all the way up until your chin passes the be bar.

exercises.name: Diamond push-ups
exercises.description: Get into a high plank position, placing your hands close together so your thumbs and index fingers touch. Keeping your body straight and core engaged, lower your body while keeping your elbows close to your body. Push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Inverted rows
exercises.description: Set a bar in a rack to about waist height. You can also use a smith machine. Take a wider than shoulder-width grip on the bar and position yourself hanging underneath the bar. Your body should be straight with your heels on the ground. Your arms should be fully extended. This will be your starting position. Now pull yourself up to the bar until your chest touches the bar. Lower yourself back down to the starting position.

exercises.name: AMRAP Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Place your hands firmly on the ground, directly under shoulders. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Push your body up back to the starting position. Do as many reps as possible (AMRAP) in 30 minutes.

exercises.name: AMRAP Dips
exercises.description: Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your hands just outside of your hips. Walk your feet out a few steps, slide your butt off the bench, and straighten your arms. Bend your elbows and lower your body until your arms are bent at about 90 degrees. Push yourself back up to the starting position. Do as many reps as possible (AMRAP) in 30 minutes.

exercises.name: AMRAP Diamond Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position but with your hands close together so your thumbs and index fingers touch. This is the 'diamond' shape. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Push your body up back to the starting position. Do as many reps as possible (AMRAP) in 30 minutes.

exercises.name: Barbell Bicep Curls
exercises.description: Stand up with your torso upright while holding a barbell at a shoulder-width grip. The palm of your hands should be facing forward and the elbows should be close to the torso. This will be your starting position. While holding the upper arms stationary, curl the weights while contracting the biceps as you breathe out. Continue the movement until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. Hold the contracted position for a second as you squeeze the biceps. Slowly begin to bring the bar back to starting position as your breathe in. Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
exercises.description: Hold onto the bars of a dip station and push yourself up to the top position. Lean forward slightly and let your elbows flare out slightly. Lower your body until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. Push yourself back up to the top position and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Skull Crushers
exercises.description: Lie back on a flat bench. Using a close grip, lift the barbell and hold it straight over you with your arms fully extended. This will be your starting position. Slowly lower the bar by bending at the elbows while keeping your upper arms stationary until the bar is just above your forehead. Contract your triceps and push the bar back to the starting position. Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.

exercises.name: Hammer Curls with Medicine Ball
exercises.description: Stand up with your torso upright and a medicine ball in each hand being held at arms length. The elbows should be close to the torso. This will be your starting position. While holding the upper arm stationary, curl the weights while contracting the biceps as you breathe out. Continue the movement until your biceps are fully contracted and the medicine balls are at shoulder level. Hold the contracted position for a second as you squeeze the biceps. Slowly begin to bring the medicine balls back to starting position as your breathe in. Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: With your hands shoulder-width apart, lower your body until your chest almost touches the floor. Push your body back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Pull-ups
exercises.description: Grasp the pull-up bar with an overhand grip, then pull your body up until your chin is above the bar. Lower your body back down to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dips
exercises.description: Hold on to parallel bars with your body at arm's length above the bars. Lower your body until your shoulders are below your elbows. Push back up until your arms are straight.

exercises.name: Diamond Push-ups
exercises.description: Place your hands close together so your thumbs and index fingers touch. Lower your body until your chest almost touches the floor. Push your body back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Chin-ups
exercises.description: Grasp the pull-up bar with an underhand grip, then pull your body up until your chin is above the bar. Lower your body back down to the starting position.

exercises.name: Pushups
exercises.description: Hands should be shoulder-width apart. Lower your body until your chest touches the floor. Push your body back up while maintaining a straight body line.

exercises.name: Chin-ups
exercises.description: Grab the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. Pull your body up until your chin is over the bar. Lower your body back down in a controlled manner.

exercises.name: Bicep Curls (Dumbbell)
exercises.description: Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand. Keep the elbows close to the torso. Curl the weights while contracting your biceps. Only the forearms should move.

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
exercises.description: Hold on to a dip bar or two parallel bars with your palms facing inward and your arms straight. Lower your body until your shoulders are below your elbows. Push yourself back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Hammer Curls (Dumbbell)
exercises.description: Stand up with your torso upright while holding a dumbbell in each hand. The palms of the hands should be facing your torso. Curl the right weight as you keep the upper arm stationary.

exercises.name: Tricep Extension (Barbell)
exercises.description: Stand up with a barbell held with both hands. The palms of your hands should be facing up. Use your biceps to curl the weights up to shoulder level.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Place hands firmly on the ground, directly under shoulders. Lower your body until your chest grazes the floor. Push back up.

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
exercises.description: Sit on a chair or bench. Slide your bottom off the bench and hold yourself up with arms straightened. Bend your arms to a 90-degree angle. Push back up to start.

exercises.name: Arm Circles
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Extend your arms out to the sides at shoulder height. Start making small circles with your arms. Keep the circles small to engage the triceps and shoulder muscles.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Curl
exercises.description: Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand at arm's length. Keep your elbows close to your torso and rotate the palms of your hands until they are facing forward. Now, keeping the upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. Then, inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
exercises.description: Hold on to a barbell with your palms facing down and your hands about shoulder-width apart. Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it straight over you with your arms fully extended. This will be your starting position. As you breathe in, come down slowly until you feel the bar on your lower chest. After a second pause, bring the bar back to the starting position as you breathe out and push the bar using your triceps muscles.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Slam
exercises.description: Hold a medicine ball with both hands and stand with your feet at shoulder width. Lift the ball above your head while fully extending your body. Reverse the motion, slamming the ball into the ground directly in front of you as hard as you can. Pick the ball up and repeat the movement.

exercises.name: Close-Grip Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lay on a flat bench holding a barbell using a close (about shoulder width) grip. Lift the bar from the rack and hold it straight over your chest with your arms full extended. As you breathe in, come down slowly until you feel the bar on your middle chest. After a second pause, bring the bar back to the starting position as you breathe out and push the bar using your triceps muscles.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Bicep Curl
exercises.description: Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended, and palms facing your torso. Keep your elbows close to your torso at all times. Curl the weights while contracting your biceps.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Tricep Extension
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell at one end and use both hands to cup the opposite end. Lift the dumbbell over your head so your arms are extended. Keep your elbows in close to your head and perform the exercise by lowering the dumbbell behind your head and raising it back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Hammer Curl
exercises.description: Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended, and palms facing your torso. This will be your starting position. Now, while keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Skull Crusher
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench with a dumbbell on each hand resting on top of your thighs. The palms of your hand will be facing each other. Using your thighs to help raise the dumbbells, lift the dumbbells one at a time so you can hold them in front of you at shoulder width. Lower the weight slowly back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Concentration Curl
exercises.description: Sit on the end of a flat bench with your legs spread. Place a dumbbell in front of you between your legs. Use your right arm to pick up the dumbbell. Place the back of your right upper arm on the top of your inner right thigh. Curl the weight while contracting your biceps as you breathe out.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Kickback
exercises.description: Start with a dumbbell in each hand and your palms facing your torso. Keep your back straight with a slight bend in the knees and bend forward at the waist. Your torso should be almost parallel to the floor. Make sure to keep your head up. Your upper arms should be close to your torso and parallel to the floor. Your forearms should be pointed towards the floor as you hold the weights. There should be a 90-degree angle formed between your upper arm and forearm. Kick back the weight while exhaling and extend your arm fully.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Zottman Curl
exercises.description: Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand at arm's length. Your elbows should be close to your torso. This will be your starting position. Now, while keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Overhead Tricep Extension
exercises.description: Stand up straight with a dumbbell in your hand and your feet hip-width apart. Lift the dumbbell above your head until your arm is fully extended. Keep your elbows close to your head and perform the exercise by lowering the dumbbell behind your head and raising it back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Bicep Curl
exercises.description: Stand up with your torso upright while holding a barbell at a shoulder-width grip. Curl the weights while contracting your biceps as you breathe out. Only the forearms should move.

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
exercises.description: Hold on to a bench or chair with your body at arm’s length. Lower your body towards the floor with your elbows at about a 90-degree angle. Using your triceps lift yourself back to the start position.

exercises.name: Hammer Curls
exercises.description: Stand up with your torso upright and a dumbbell in each hand being held at arms length. While holding the upper arms stationary, curl the weights while contracting the biceps as you breathe out.

exercises.name: Skull Crushers
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench while holding a barbell on your hands. Lower the bar by using your elbows and while keeping your upper arm stationary. Return to the starting position using your tricep muscles.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Clean
exercises.description: Start with a kettlebell between your feet. Pull the kettlebell up to your shoulder while rotating your wrist until your palm faces forward.

exercises.name: Close-Grip Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie back on a flat bench. Using a close grip, lift the bar from the rack and hold it straight over you. As you breathe in, come down slowly until you feel the bar on your middle chest. After a second pause, bring the bar back to the starting position as you breathe out.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Kickback
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in one hand, hinge at the hips and let the arm hang perpendicular to the floor. Keep your arm close to your torso, lift the dumbbell back by extending your elbow and allow it to slowly return after a short pause.

exercises.name: Preacher Curl
exercises.description: Perform this using a barbell, resting your arms on the preacher bench for support. Lift the barbell by flexing at the elbow joint until your arms are fully flexed. Return to the starting position.

exercises.name: Push-Ups
exercises.description: Get into a high plank position. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Pause, then push yourself back up.

exercises.name: Diamond Push-Ups
exercises.description: Start in a push-up position, but with your hands touching so your thumbs and index fingers form a diamond. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches your hands. Pause, then push yourself back up.

exercises.name: Dips
exercises.description: Hold onto the parallel bars of a dip station, jump up to straighten your arms, lower your body until your elbows are at a 90-degree angle, then push back up.

exercises.name: Pull-Ups
exercises.description: Grab a pull-up bar with your palms facing away. Pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar. Lower back down.

exercises.name: Chin-Ups
exercises.description: Grab a pull-up bar with your palms facing towards you. Pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar. Lower back down.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, kettlebell in front of feet. Hinge at hips to grab kettlebell with both hands, then stand, keeping back straight. Lower weight back down.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Swing
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, kettlebell in front of feet. Hinge at hips to grab kettlebell with both hands, then swing it back between legs. Using hip drive, stand and swing kettlebell up to chest level. Swing it back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell High Pull
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, kettlebell in front of feet. Squat down and grab kettlebell with one hand. As you stand, pull the kettlebell up to shoulder height, leading with your elbow. Lower it back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Row
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, a kettlebell in each hand. Hinge at the hips and let your arms hang down. Pull the kettlebells up to your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. Lower them back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Clean and Press
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, kettlebell in front of feet. Squat down and grab kettlebell with one hand. Stand and pull kettlebell up to shoulder height, then press it overhead. Lower it back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Pull ups
exercises.description: Hang from a bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder width. Pull yourself up until your chin is level with the bar, then slowly lower back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Inverted Row
exercises.description: Set a bar in a rack at waist height. Grab the bar with a wider than shoulder-width grip, palms facing away from you. Hang underneath the bar with your body straight. Pull yourself up to the bar, then lower back down.

exercises.name: Push ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Push your body back up.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, toes pointing forward. Lower your body as far as you can by pushing your hips back and bending your knees. Pause, then slowly push yourself back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Push-Ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Pause at the bottom, and then push back up to the starting position as quickly as possible.

exercises.name: Battle Ropes
exercises.description: Hold the ends of the rope at arm's length in front of your hips with your hands shoulder-width apart. Brace your core and begin alternately raising and lowering each arm explosively. Keep alternating arms for the desired number of reps.

exercises.name: Barbell Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with your mid-foot under the barbell. Bend over and grab the bar with a shoulder-width grip. Bend your knees until your shins touch the bar. Lift your chest up and straighten your lower back. Take a deep breath, hold it, and stand up with the weight.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Row
exercises.description: Bend over at your hips and knees, grab a dumbbell with one hand. Pull the dumbbell to your side until your elbow is above your back. Lower it back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Bent Over Row
exercises.description: Hold a barbell at hip level. Bend your knees slightly and bring your torso forward by bending at the waist. Keep your back straight until it's almost parallel to the floor. Lift the barbell to you. Hold for a brief pause at the top and lower the barbell back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Pullover
exercises.description: Lie down on a bench. Securely position your feet flat on the floor. Extend the arms above the chest. Lower the weights in an arc behind your head. Return your arms back to the starting position and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Shrug
exercises.description: Stand up straight with your feet at shoulder width. Hold the barbell with both hands in front of you using a pronated grip. Lift the barbell by elevating the shoulders as high as possible while you exhale. Hold the contraction at the top for a second.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Rear Delt Row
exercises.description: Bend at the hips until your torso is nearly parallel to the floor. Let the dumbbells hang at arm's length from your shoulders, your palms facing in. Bend your elbows and lift the dumbbells to the sides of your torso.

exercises.name: Barbell High Pull
exercises.description: Grab a barbell with an overhand grip that is slightly wider than shoulder width. Set your feet at hip width. Lower the bar to knee level. Now, explosively stand and shrug, pulling the bar straight up in front of your torso.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Hammer Curl
exercises.description: Stand up with your torso upright and a dumbbell in each hand being held at arms length. The elbows should be close to the torso. While holding the upper arm stationary, curl the weights while contracting the biceps as you breathe out.

exercises.name: Barbell Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with your mid-foot under the barbell. Bend over and grab the bar with a shoulder-width grip. Bend your knees until your shins touch the bar. Lift your chest up and straighten your lower back. Take a deep breath, hold it, and stand up with the weight.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Bent Over Row
exercises.description: Holding a dumbbell in each hand bend your knees slightly and bring your torso forward, by bending at the waist, while keeping the back straight until it is almost parallel to the floor. Keep the elbows close to the body and only the forearms should move. Squeeze your back muscles and hold for a brief pause then lower the weights.

exercises.name: Barbell Bent Over Row
exercises.description: Hold a barbell with a grip slightly wider than shoulder width, with your palms facing down. Bend your knees slightly and bring your torso forward by bending at the waist. While keeping the back straight, lift the barbell to you. Keep the elbows close to the body. Only the forearms should move.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Pullover
exercises.description: Lie down on a bench with a dumbbell in both hands, palms facing up. Extend your arms above your chest, but don’t lock your elbows. Lower the weights in an arc behind your head while keeping your arms straight. Lift the dumbbell back over your chest, in the same arc.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Shrug
exercises.description: Stand up straight with a dumbbell on each hand. Lift the dumbbells by elevating the shoulders as high as possible while you exhale. Hold the contraction at the top for a second. Lower the dumbbells back to the original position.

exercises.name: Barbell High Pull
exercises.description: Stand over the barbell with the balls of your feet positioned under the bar. Bend at the hips and knees and grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands just outside your knees. Pull the bar up off the floor by extending your hips and knees. As the bar reaches knee level, pull the bar up and to your shoulders by extending through the hips and knees while simultaneously shrugging your shoulders.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, knees slightly bent. Hold a pair of dumbbells in front of your thighs, palms facing your body. Keeping your knees slightly bent, press your hips back as you hinge at the waist and lower the dumbbells to just below your knees. Push your body back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Upright Row
exercises.description: Grasp a barbell with an overhand grip that is slightly less than shoulder width. The bar should be resting on the top of your thighs with your arms extended and a slight bend in your elbows. Your back should also be straight. Use your side shoulders to lift the bar as you exhale. The bar should be close to the body as you move it up. Continue to lift it until it nearly touches your chin.

exercises.name: Pull-ups
exercises.description: Hang from a bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar. Lower yourself back down in a controlled manner.

exercises.name: Barbell Deadlifts
exercises.description: Stand in front of a loaded barbell. Bend at your hips and knees, grab the bar with an overhand grip. Keep your lower back naturally arched, pull your torso up and thrust your hips forward, lifting the bar. Lower the bar to the floor.

exercises.name: Chin-ups
exercises.description: Hang from a bar with your hands shoulder-width apart and palms facing towards you. Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar. Lower yourself back down in a controlled manner.

exercises.name: Barbell Rows
exercises.description: Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, bend at your hips and knees, and lower your torso until it's almost parallel to the floor. Pull the bar to your upper abs. Lower the bar.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Rows
exercises.description: Set a bar at hip height in a Smith machine or power rack. Hang underneath the bar with your body straight. Pull your chest to the bar. Lower yourself back down in a controlled manner.

exercises.name: Barbell Shrugs
exercises.description: Stand upright holding a barbell in front of your body at waist height with a overhand grip. Raise your shoulders up towards your ears as far as possible. Lower them back down.

exercises.name: Inverted Rows
exercises.description: Set a bar at waist height. Position yourself under the bar in a hanging position with your body straight. Pull your chest up to the bar. Lower yourself back down.

exercises.name: T-Bar Rows
exercises.description: Position yourself over the bar, and grab it with one hand on each handle. Lift the bar off the floor, tilting your pelvis forward. Pull the bar towards your chest, then lower it back down.

exercises.name: Barbell Deadlifts
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart with the barbell over your mid-foot. Bend at the hips and knees to grab the barbell with an overhand grip. Keep your back in a neutral position. Push through your heels to lift the weight up, keeping it close to your body. Extend your hips and knees. Return the weight to the ground by pushing your hips back and bending your knees.

exercises.name: Pull-ups
exercises.description: Hang from a pull-up bar with your hands a bit wider than shoulder-width apart. Pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar. Lower yourself back down with control.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Rows
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, bend your knees slightly and bring your torso forward by bending at the waist. Keep the back straight until it's almost parallel to the floor. Lift the dumbbells to your side, keeping the elbows close to the body. Lower the dumbbells back down.

exercises.name: Inverted Bodyweight Rows
exercises.description: Set a bar at hip height. Hold the bar with an overhand grip, hands wider than shoulder-width apart. Walk your feet forward so you're hanging beneath the bar in a straight line. Pull your chest up to the bar. Lower yourself back down with control.

exercises.name: Barbell Bent Over Rows
exercises.description: Hold a barbell using a pronated grip. Bend your knees slightly and bring your torso forward, by bending at the waist, while keeping the back straight. Lift the barbell to you. Keep the elbows close to the body. Lower the barbell back down.

exercises.name: Hanging Leg Raises
exercises.description: Hang from a pull-up bar with your legs fully extended. Keep your torso stationary, breathe out and lift your legs until your torso makes a 90-degree angle with your legs. Lower your legs back down.

exercises.name: T-bar Row
exercises.description: Position a bar into a landmine or in a corner to keep it from moving. Load an appropriate weight onto your end. Stand over the bar, and position a Double D row handle around the bar next to the collar. Using your hips and legs, rise to a standing position. Assume a wide stance with your hips back and your chest up. Pull the weight to your upper abdomen by retracting the shoulder blades and flexing the elbows. Return until the weight caroms the floor.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Pullovers
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench holding a dumbbell with both hands, extending it above your chest. Lower the weight behind your head, bending at the elbows slightly. Pull the dumbbell back over your chest.

exercises.name: Pull-ups
exercises.description: Grab the bar with your palms facing forward, pull your body up until your chin is above the bar, then lower your body back down.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Rows
exercises.description: Set a bar at waist height, lie underneath it, grab it with both hands, and pull your chest up to the bar.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Place your hands shoulder-width apart, lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor, then push back up.

exercises.name: Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, bend your knees and hips to lower your body as far as you can, then push back up.

exercises.name: Barbell Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with your mid-foot under the barbell. Bend over and grab the bar with a shoulder-width grip. Bend your knees until your shins touch the bar. Lift your chest up and straighten your lower back. Take a deep breath, hold it, and stand up with the weight.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Bent Over Row
exercises.description: Stand tall with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso. Keep your back straight and slightly bend the knees while leaning forward from the waist. Your torso should be close to parallel with the floor. Lift the dumbbells straight up to the chest, keeping the arms close to the body. Lower weights back down.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Swing
exercises.description: Stand up straight, with feet a bit wider than hip-distance apart. Grab the handle with both hands, keeping the palms face down and arms in front of the body. Maintain a slight bend to the knee and drive the hips back, lowering the body. Then, in a fluid motion, explosively drive the hips forward while swinging the kettlebell, keeping the glutes and core engaged.

exercises.name: Barbell Shrug
exercises.description: Stand up straight with your feet at shoulder width as you hold a barbell with both hands in front of you using a pronated grip. Lift the barbell straight up by raising your shoulders and try to touch your ears with your shoulders. Pause at the top, then lower the barbell back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Pull Over
exercises.description: Lie perpendicular to the bench with only your shoulders lying on the surface. Hips should be below the bench and legs bent with feet firmly on the floor. Extend the arms above the chest with a dumbbell in both hands. Lower the weight in an arc behind your head while keeping your arms straight. Pull the dumbbell back over your head to the starting position.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Renegade Row
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position with your hands grasping two kettlebells. Keep your hands shoulder-width apart, back flat, and feet slightly wider than hip-width apart. Pull one kettlebell up towards your lower ribs while keeping your core tight and hips parallel to the floor. Lower the kettlebell back down and repeat on the other side.

exercises.name: Barbell Bent Over Row
exercises.description: Hold a barbell with a pronated grip (palms facing down). Bend your knees slightly and bring your torso forward, by bending at the waist, while keeping the back straight. Keep the head up. The barbell should hang directly in front of you. While keeping the torso stationary, lift the barbell. Keep the elbows close to the body. Lower back down.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended, and palms facing your body. Keep your chest up, pull your shoulders back and look straight ahead. Lower your body by bending from the hips and bending your knees, keep moving forward as if you were going to pick something from the floor until you feel a stretch on your hamstrings. Lift back up.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, dumbbells in front of thighs. Bend at the hips and knees, and grab the dumbbells with an overhand grip. Keep your chest up and your back straight as you stand up straight and lift the dumbbells to waist height. Lower the dumbbells back to the floor by pushing your hips back and bending your knees.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Bent Over Row
exercises.description: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Bend at your hips and knees, brace your abs, and lower your torso until it's almost parallel to the floor. Pull the dumbbells to your ribs as you squeeze your shoulder blades together.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Pullover
exercises.description: Lie on your back on a bench. Hold a dumbbell with both hands above your chest. Keeping your arms straight, lower the weight behind your head. Pull the dumbbell back over your chest.

exercises.name: Single Arm Dumbbell Row
exercises.description: Place one knee on a bench, palm down. Hold a dumbbell in your other hand, arm hanging down and palm facing inwards. Pull the dumbbell up to your side until your elbow is at a 90-degree angle. Lower back down.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Back Fly
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Bend at your hips and knees, brace your abs, and lower your torso until it's almost parallel to the floor. Raise both arms out to the sides as you squeeze your shoulder blades together.

exercises.name: Renegade Rows
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position holding the dumbbells. Pull one dumbbell up to your hip, keeping your core tight and your back flat. Lower the dumbbell and repeat on the other side.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Shrugs
exercises.description: Stand tall with a dumbbell in each hand at your sides, palms facing your body. Keeping your arms straight, shrug your shoulders as high as you can. Pause at the top, then lower back down.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Reverse Fly
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. Bend at your waist, lowering your torso until it's almost parallel to the floor. Raise the dumbbells out to the sides, squeezing your shoulder blades together.

exercises.name: Pull-ups
exercises.description: Hang from a bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar. Lower yourself back down with control.

exercises.name: Inverted Rows
exercises.description: Set a bar in a rack to waist height. Grab the bar with a wider than shoulder-width grip and hang underneath. Your body should be straight with your heels on the ground. Pull your chest up to the bar.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Keeping your body straight, lower your body until your chest touches the floor. Push your body up returning to the starting position.

exercises.name: Pike Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a pike position with your feet hip-width apart and your hands shoulder-width apart. Lower your body until your head nearly touches the floor. Push your body back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with your mid-foot under the bar. Bend over and grab the bar. Bend your knees until your shins touch the bar. Lift your chest up and straighten your lower back. Take a deep breath, hold it, and stand up with the weight.

exercises.name: Bent Over Row
exercises.description: Hold a barbell with a pronated grip (palms facing down). Bend your knees slightly and bring your torso forward, by bending at the waist, while keeping the back straight until it is almost parallel to the floor. The barbell should hang directly in front of you as your arms hang perpendicular to the floor and your torso. This is your starting position. Now, while keeping the torso stationary, breathe out and lift the barbell to you. Keep the elbows close to the body and only use the forearms to hold the weight. At the top contracted position, squeeze the back muscles and hold for a brief pause. Then inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Shrug
exercises.description: Stand up straight with your feet at shoulder width as you hold a barbell with both hands in front of you using a pronated grip (palms facing the thighs). Your hands should be a little wider than shoulder width apart. You can use wrist wraps for this exercise for a better grip. This will be your starting position. Raise your shoulders up as far as you can go as you breathe out and hold the contraction for a second. Refrain from trying to lift the barbell by using your biceps. Slowly return to the starting position as you breathe in.

exercises.name: Barbell Pullover
exercises.description: Lie back on a flat bench. Using a close grip (around shoulder width), lift the bar from the rack and hold it straight over you with your arms locked. This will be your starting position. While keeping your arms locked in the contracted position, lower it slowly in an arc behind your head while breathing in. Attempt to go as low as possible without bending the arms. Bring the bar back to the starting position as you breathe out and push the bar using your chest muscles. Lock your arms in the contracted position, squeeze your chest, hold for a second and then start coming down slowly.

exercises.name: T-Bar Row
exercises.description: Position a bar into a landmine or in a corner to keep it from moving. Load an appropriate weight onto your end. Stand over the bar, and position a Double D row handle around the bar next to the collar. Using your hips and legs, rise to a standing position. Assume a wide stance with your hips back and your chest up. Your arms should be extended. This will be your starting position. Pull the weight to your upper abdomen by retracting the shoulder blades and flexing the elbows. Do not jerk the weight or cheat during the movement, and keep the back straight. Pause at the top of the movement, and then slowly lower the weight back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Seated Cable Row
exercises.description: For this exercise you will need access to a low pulley row machine with a V-bar. Note: The V-bar will enable you to have a neutral grip where the palms of your hands face each other. To get into the starting position, first sit down on the machine and place your feet on the front platform or crossbar provided making sure that your knees are slightly bent and not locked. Lean over as you keep the natural alignment of your back and grab the V-bar handles. With your arms extended pull back until your torso is at a 90-degree angle from your legs. Your back should be slightly arched and your chest should be sticking out. You should be feeling a nice stretch on your lats as you hold the bar in front of you. This is the starting position of the exercise.

exercises.name: Barbell Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with your mid-foot under the barbell. Bend over and grab the bar with a shoulder-width grip. Bend your knees until your shins touch the bar. Lift your chest up and straighten your lower back. Take a deep breath, hold it, and stand up with the weight.

exercises.name: Pull-ups
exercises.description: Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing forward. Pull yourself up until your chin is over the bar. Lower your body back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Bent Over Rows
exercises.description: Stand with your mid-foot under the barbell. Bend over and grab the bar with a shoulder-width grip. Bend your knees slightly and keep your back straight. Pull the bar to your lower chest. Lower the bar to the starting position.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Slams
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a medicine ball with both hands. Lift the ball overhead, then slam it down to the ground as hard as you can. Squat to pick the ball up and repeat.

exercises.name: Pull Ups
exercises.description: Hang from a pull-up bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Pull your body up until your chin is above the bar. Lower your body back down in a controlled motion.

exercises.name: Pike Push Ups
exercises.description: Start in a pushup position, then lift your hips to create an upside-down V with your body. Bend your elbows to lower your head toward the ground. Push back up.

exercises.name: Inverted Rows
exercises.description: Set a bar in a rack to waist height. Grab the bar with a wider than shoulder-width grip and hang underneath. Position yourself with heels out in front of you and arms fully extended. Begin by pulling your chest to the bar. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward.

exercises.name: Superman
exercises.description: Lie face down on the floor, arms extended straight above your head. Lift your chest, arms and legs off the floor by arching your back. Hold for a second, then lower back down.

exercises.name: Push Ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Place hands firmly on the ground, directly under shoulders. Lower your body. Push your body up.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench holding a dumbbell in each hand. Press the weights up above your chest, then lower them back to the start under control.

exercises.name: Barbell Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet a little wider than shoulder-width apart. Hold a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip. Lower your body as far as you can by pushing your hips back and bending your knees. Pause, then slowly push yourself back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lunges
exercises.description: Stand upright, feet together, and take a controlled step forward with your right leg. Lower hips toward the floor and bend both knees (almost at 90-degree angles). The back knee should come close but never touch the ground. Your front knee should be directly over the ankle and the back knee should be pointing down toward the floor.

exercises.name: Burpees
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, weight in your heels, and your arms at your sides. Push your hips back, bend your knees, and lower your body into a squat. Place your hands on the floor directly in front of, and just inside, your feet. Shift your weight onto your hands.

exercises.name: Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench holding a barbell in the rack above you with a shoulder-width, overhand grip. Lift the bar off the rack and position it above your chest with arms fully extended. From the starting position, breathe in and lower the bar slowly until it skims the middle of your chest. Push the bar back to the starting position explosively as you breathe out. That’s one rep.

exercises.name: Incline Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Sit on an incline bench with the barbell racked behind your head. Grab the bar with an overhand grip, hands just wider than shoulder-width apart, then lift it off the rack and hold it above your chest with your arms fully extended. Lower the bar directly to your chest, then press it back to the start.

exercises.name: Barbell Decline Bench Press
exercises.description: Set an adjustable bench to a 30°-45° decline and lie back on it with a barbell racked on your chest. Hold the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Unrack the bar and hold it above your chest with your arms fully extended. Lower the bar to your chest, then press it back to the start.

exercises.name: Close-Grip Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie back on a flat bench holding a barbell with a narrow, overhand grip. From the starting position, breathe in and lower the bar slowly until it skims the middle of your chest. Push the bar back to the starting position explosively as you breathe out. That’s one rep.

exercises.name: Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie back on a flat bench. Using a medium width grip, lift the bar from the rack and hold it straight over you with your arms locked. As you breathe in, come down slowly until you feel the bar on your middle chest. Push the bar back to the starting position as you breathe out. Repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Fly
exercises.description: Lie flat on your back with a kettlebell in each hand. Extend your arms out to your sides, then bring the kettlebells back up to meet above your chest. Repeat.

exercises.name: Incline Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Sit back on an incline bench with a barbell in your hands at shoulder width. Lift the bar from the rack and hold it straight over your chest with your arms full extended. As you breathe in, lower the bar slowly until it skims the middle of your chest. Push the bar back to the starting position as you breathe out. Repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Pullover
exercises.description: Lie flat on your back holding a kettlebell with both hands, arms extended over your chest. Keeping your arms straight, lower the weight behind your head, then lift it back to the starting position. Repeat.

exercises.name: Decline Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Secure your legs at the end of the decline bench and slowly lay down on the bench. Using a medium width grip, lift the bar from the rack and hold it straight over you with your arms locked. As you breathe in, come down slowly until you feel the bar on your lower chest. Push the bar back to the starting position as you breathe out. Repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Push-up
exercises.description: Place two kettlebells on the ground at shoulder width. Grab onto the handles and perform a push-up, lowering your chest to just above the ground and pushing back up to the starting position. Repeat.

exercises.name: Close-Grip Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie back on a flat bench. Using a close grip, lift the bar from the rack and hold it straight over you with your arms locked. This will be your starting position. As you breathe in, come down slowly until you feel the bar on your middle chest. Push the bar back to the starting position as you breathe out. Repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Floor Press
exercises.description: Lie on your back on the floor with a kettlebell in each hand. Press the kettlebells up until your arms are fully extended, then lower them back to the starting position. Repeat.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in high plank position. Keeping your body straight, lower your body until your chest almost touches the floor. Push your body back up to the starting position. Repeat.

exercises.name: Dips
exercises.description: Place your hands shoulder-width apart on a secured bench or stable chair. Slide your butt off the front of the bench with your legs extended out in front of you. Lower your body until your shoulder joints are below your elbows. Push back up until your elbows are nearly straight but not locked. Repeat.

exercises.name: Incline Push-ups
exercises.description: Stand facing bench or sturdy elevated platform. Place hands on edge of bench or platform, slightly wider than shoulder width. Position forefoot back from bench or platform with arms and body straight. Lower chest down to bench or platform by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

exercises.name: Decline Push-ups
exercises.description: Place your feet on a raised surface, such as a box or bench, with your hands on the floor. Maintain a straight body line as you lower your chest to the floor. Push up to the starting position and repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Chest Press
exercises.description: Lay on your back with a kettlebell in each hand. Push the kettlebells up until your arms are fully extended, then lower them back down to your chest.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Push Ups
exercises.description: Place one hand on the medicine ball and the other on the floor, perform a push up. Roll the ball to the other hand and repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Fly
exercises.description: Lay on your back holding a kettlebell in each hand. With a slight bend in your elbows, lower your arms out to the sides until they're level with your chest. Bring them back up to the top.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Chest Pass
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart and hold the medicine ball at chest height. Pass the ball quickly from your chest to a wall or a partner, then catch it on its return.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Pullover
exercises.description: Lay on your back with a kettlebell in both hands. Reach the kettlebell back behind your head then bring it back over your chest.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Slams
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart and hold the medicine ball overhead. Slam the ball down to the ground as hard as you can. Squat to pick it up and repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Seated Press
exercises.description: Sit on the floor with a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height. Push the kettlebells up until your arms are fully extended, then lower them back to your shoulders.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Diamond Push Ups
exercises.description: Place both hands on the medicine ball under your chest. Perform a push up, keeping your hands close together to form a diamond shape.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Place hands firmly on the ground, directly under shoulders. Lower your body until your chest is an inch from the ground then explosively drive up by fully extending your arms.

exercises.name: Kettlebell swings
exercises.description: Stand up straight, with feet a bit wider than hip-distance apart. Grab the handle with both hands, keeping the palms face down and arms in front of the body. Maintain a slight bend in the knees and drive the hips back, lowering the body but not too low. Then, in a fluid motion, explosively drive the hips forward while swinging the kettlebell, keeping the glutes and core engaged.

exercises.name: Battle ropes
exercises.description: Stand facing the anchor. Grab the ends of the ropes in each hand with your palms facing each other. Bend your knees slightly and start making waves with the ropes by raising and lowering your arms alternately.

exercises.name: Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie back on a flat bench. Using a medium width grip, lift the bar from the rack and hold it straight over your body. Lower it slowly to your chest, then push it back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Incline Bench Press
exercises.description: Set an adjustable bench to an incline of 30-45 degrees. Lie back on the bench and lift the bar from the rack, holding it straight over your body. Lower it slowly to your chest, then push it back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Flyes
exercises.description: Lie back on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand. Extend your arms fully at a slight angle away from your body. Lower the weights slowly in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest, then bring the weights back together in a hugging motion.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Pullovers
exercises.description: Lie back on a flat bench with a kettlebell in both hands, arms extended over your chest. Lower the weight in an arc behind your head, keeping your arms straight, then lift it back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Pullover
exercises.description: Lie back on a flat bench with a dumbbell in both hands, arms extended over your chest. Lower the weight in an arc behind your head, keeping your arms straight, then lift it back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Chest Press
exercises.description: Lie back on a flat bench with a kettlebell in each hand, arms extended over your chest. Lower the weights to your chest, then press them back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Decline Bench Press
exercises.description: Set an adjustable bench to a decline and secure your legs at the end of the bench. Lift the bar from the rack and hold it straight over your body. Lower it slowly to your chest, then push it back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Decline Flyes
exercises.description: Set an adjustable bench to a decline and secure your legs at the end. Hold a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended over your chest. Lower the weights in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest, then bring them back together.

exercises.name: Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on your back on a bench. Grip the bar with hands just wider than shoulder-width apart. Lower the bar until it's at nipple level, then push the bar back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Fly
exercises.description: Lie on your back on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand. Extend your arms above you with a slight bend at the elbows. Lower the weights until your elbows are even with your shoulders. Keep the same bend in your elbows as you press the weights back up.

exercises.name: Incline Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Sit on an incline bench with the barbell racked above your head. Grab the bar with a grip slightly wider than shoulder width. Unrack the bar and lower it to your chest. Push the bar back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Incline Dumbbell Fly
exercises.description: Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand. Extend your arms above you with a slight bend at the elbows. Lower the weights until your elbows are even with your shoulders. Keep the same bend in your elbows as you press the weights back up.

exercises.name: Decline Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie down on a decline bench with the barbell racked above your head. Grab the bar with a grip slightly wider than shoulder width. Unrack the bar and lower it to your chest. Push the bar back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Decline Dumbbell Fly
exercises.description: Lie on a decline bench with a dumbbell in each hand. Extend your arms above you with a slight bend at the elbows. Lower the weights until your elbows are even with your shoulders. Keep the same bend in your elbows as you press the weights back up.

exercises.name: Close-Grip Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on your back on a bench. Grip the bar with hands just shoulder-width apart. Lower the bar until it's at nipple level, then push the bar back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Pullover
exercises.description: Lie on your back on a bench with a dumbbell in both hands above your chest. Keeping your arms slightly bent, lower the weight behind your head. Pull the weight back over your chest.

exercises.name: Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie down on your back on a bench and hold a barbell over your chest. Lower it to your mid-chest and then press it back up to the start.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Flyes
exercises.description: Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand resting on your thighs. Lift the dumbbells to shoulder height, palms facing in. With a slight bend in your elbows, lower your arms out to the sides until you feel a stretch in your chest. Return to the starting position.

exercises.name: Incline Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Sit on an incline bench and hold a barbell at shoulder width. Lower the barbell to your upper chest and then press it back up to the start.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Pullover
exercises.description: Lie on a bench, holding a dumbbell with both hands above your chest. Lower the weight behind your head, then bring it back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Decline Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on a decline bench and hold a barbell at shoulder width. Lower the barbell to your lower chest and then press it back up to the start.

exercises.name: Close Grip Dumbbell Press
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench holding two dumbbells at your shoulders, palms facing each other. Press the weights up until your arms are fully extended, then lower them back to the start.

exercises.name: Flat Dumbbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench holding two dumbbells at your shoulders. Press the weights up until your arms are fully extended, then lower them back to the start.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Chest Fly
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench holding two dumbbells directly above your chest with your palms facing each other. With a slight bend in your elbows, lower your arms out to the sides until you feel a stretch in your chest. Return to the starting position.

exercises.name: Push-Ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Place hands firmly on the ground, directly under shoulders. Lower your body. Push your body up returning to the starting position.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Chest Pass
exercises.description: Hold a medicine ball at chest level. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart. Push the medicine ball out as quickly as possible, catching it on the rebound.

exercises.name: Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie back on a bench. Grab a barbell with hands slightly wider than shoulder-width. Lower the barbell to your chest then press it back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Diamond Push-Ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Place hands close together so your thumbs and index fingers touch. Lower your body and push up back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Incline Dumbbell Fly
exercises.description: Lie on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand. Extend arms above you. Lower the dumbbells to your sides maintaining the slight bend in your elbows. Bring the dumbbells back together at the top.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Push-Ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position with the medicine ball under one hand. Perform a push-up. Roll the ball to your other hand and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench holding a barbell in the rack above you with a shoulder-width, overhand grip. From a position with your arms fully extended, lower the bar slowly to your chest. Push the bar back to the starting position explosively.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Chest Pass
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Hold a medicine ball at chest level. Push the ball out from your chest, throwing it straight ahead as far as you can.

exercises.name: Barbell Incline Bench Press
exercises.description: Set an adjustable bench to an incline of 30-45 degrees. Lie on your back on the bench and hold a barbell at shoulder-width. Lower the bar to your chest, then press it back up to the start.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Slams
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and a medicine ball held overhead. Slam the ball down to the ground in front of you as hard as you can. Pick the ball up and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Decline Bench Press
exercises.description: Set an adjustable bench to a decline and lie on it. Hold a barbell at shoulder-width and lower it to your chest. Press the bar back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Chest Fly
exercises.description: Lie on your back with your hips and knees both at 90-degree angles. Using the medicine ball, reach your arms out to the sides. Keep your back flat on the floor. Raise the ball up over your chest and bring the ball upwards.

exercises.name: Barbell Floor Press
exercises.description: Lie on the floor and perform a chest press with the barbell.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench holding a dumbbell in each hand. Extend your arms straight up then lower them to the sides of your chest. Push back to the start position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Flyes
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench holding a dumbbell in each hand. Extend your arms wide open, then bring the dumbbells together above your chest.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Pullover
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench holding a dumbbell with both hands above your chest. Lower the dumbbell back over your head, then pull it back over your chest.

exercises.name: Push Ups
exercises.description: Get into a high plank position. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Push your body back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on your back on a bench. Grip the barbell with hands slightly wider than shoulder-width. Lower the bar until it's at elbow level. Push the bar back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Push Ups
exercises.description: Place one hand on the medicine ball, other on the floor. Perform a push-up. Roll the ball to the other hand and repeat.

exercises.name: Incline Dumbbell Press
exercises.description: Sit on an incline bench with dumbbells in each hand at shoulder level. Press the dumbbells up until your arms are almost fully extended. Lower them back after a short pause.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Chest Pass
exercises.description: Stand facing a wall with feet shoulder-width apart. Hold the medicine ball at chest level. Push forward to throw the ball against the wall and catch it on the rebound.

exercises.name: Decline Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on a decline bench. Grip the barbell with hands slightly wider than shoulder-width. Lower the bar until it's at elbow level. Push the bar back to the starting position.

exercises.name: One-Arm Medicine Ball Push
exercises.description: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart. Hold the medicine ball with one hand at chest level. Push forward to throw the ball and catch it with the same hand.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Flyes
exercises.description: Lie on your back with a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended up. Lower the dumbbells to your sides until you feel a stretch in your chest. Bring the dumbbells back together at the top.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Slams
exercises.description: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart. Lift the medicine ball overhead, then slam it down onto the ground as hard as possible. Squat to retrieve the ball, then stand back up.

exercises.name: Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on your back on a bench. Hold a barbell above your chest with palms facing forward and elbows bent. Press the barbell up until your arms are fully extended. Lower the barbell back to your chest and repeat.

exercises.name: Incline Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Set an adjustable bench to an incline of 30-45 degrees. Lie on your back on the bench. Hold a barbell above your chest with palms facing forward and elbows bent. Press the barbell up until your arms are fully extended. Lower the barbell back to your chest and repeat.

exercises.name: Battle Ropes
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Hold one end of the rope in each hand. Swing the ropes in an up and down motion. Continue for the desired amount of time.

exercises.name: Barbell Squats
exercises.description: Place a barbell across your shoulders, push your hips back and squat down. Push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lunges
exercises.description: Hold a pair of dumbbells at arm's length at your sides, step forward with your right leg and lower your body until your right knee is bent at least 90 degrees. Push back to the start and switch the leg.

exercises.name: Barbell Deadlifts
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, bend at your hips and knees, and grab a barbell using an overhand grip. Keeping your lower back naturally arched, pull your torso up and thrust your hips forward as you stand up with the barbell.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Calf Raises
exercises.description: Stand up straight, then push through the balls of both feet to raise your body upward. Keep your abdominal muscles pulled in so that you move straight upward, not forward or backward.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Step Ups
exercises.description: Hold a pair of dumbbells at your sides and place your right foot on a bench or step. Push your body up until your right leg is straight, then lower your body back down.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Glute Bridges
exercises.description: Lie faceup on the floor with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor. Raise your hips so your body forms a straight line from your shoulders to your knees. Pause for up to 5 seconds in the up position, then lower your body back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Front Squats
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper chest. You can either support the weight on your fingers, with wrists extended, or cross your arms to support the weight. Keeping your lower back naturally arched, bend at the hips and knees and lower your body as far as you can. Push back to the start.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Split Squats
exercises.description: Stand in a staggered stance with a dumbbell in each hand, your right foot in front of your left. Keeping your torso upright, lower your body until your right knee is bent at least 90 degrees. Push back to the start and switch the leg.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, toes pointing forward. Lower your body as far as you can by pushing your hips back and bending your knees. Pause, then slowly push yourself back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Lunges
exercises.description: Hold a medicine ball in front of your chest. Take a step forward with your right foot and lower your body until your right knee is at a 90-degree angle. Push back to the starting position and repeat with the left leg.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Calf Raises
exercises.description: Stand up straight, then push through the balls of both feet to raise your body upward. Keep your abdominal muscles pulled in so that you move straight upward, not forward or backward. Then lower back down.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Glute Bridges
exercises.description: Lie on your back with your knees bent and a medicine ball resting on your hips. Raise your hips off the ground until your knees, hips and shoulders form a straight line. Squeeze your glutes at the top, then slowly lower back to the start.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Squats
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, then lower your body as far as you can by pushing your hips back and bending your knees. Pause, then slowly push yourself back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Lunges
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your hands on your hips. Step forward with one leg and lower your body until your front knee is bent at 90 degrees. Pause, then raise up and bring your back foot forward to step forward on that foot. This completes one rep.

exercises.name: Glute Bridge
exercises.description: Lie faceup on the floor with your knees bent and your feet flat on the ground. Raise your hips so your body forms a straight line from your shoulders to your knees. Pause for up to five seconds in the up position, then lower your body back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Step-Ups
exercises.description: Place your right foot onto a sturdy box or bench, and push your body up until your right leg is straight (but not locked). Lower your body back down. That's one rep.

exercises.name: Barbell Squat
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip. Push your hips back and bend your knees to lower your body as far as you can, keeping your chest up. Push back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lunge
exercises.description: Hold a pair of dumbbells at your sides, take a step forward with your right leg and lower your body until your right knee is bent at least 90 degrees. Push yourself back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, knees slightly bent, and grab a barbell with an overhand grip. Your hands should be slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keeping your lower back naturally arched, pull your torso back and up, thrust your hips forward, and stand up with the barbell.

exercises.name: Battle Rope Waves
