exercises.description: Stand facing the anchor. Grasp the ends of the rope in each hand with your arms extended. Bracing your core and keeping your knees slightly bent, move both arms up and down rapidly, creating waves in the rope.

exercises.name: Barbell Hip Thrust
exercises.description: Sit on the ground with a bench behind you and a loaded barbell over your legs. Roll the bar so that it is directly above your hips, and lean back against the bench. Drive through your feet, extending your hips vertically through the bar. Your weight should be supported by your shoulder blades and your feet.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Step Up
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand and stand in front of a bench. Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pushing through your heel to lift your body up. Step back down and repeat with your left foot.

exercises.name: Barbell Calf Raise
exercises.description: Place a barbell across your upper back and stand with your feet hip-width apart. Push up onto your tiptoes as high as possible. Pause, then lower yourself back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Battle Rope Jumping Slams
exercises.description: Stand facing the anchor. Grasp the ends of the rope in each hand with your arms extended. Jump up, spreading your feet apart, and slam the ropes down onto the ground. Land softly, and immediately jump up again.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, hands clasped in front of chest. Push hips back and bend knees to lower into a squat. Push back up to start.

exercises.name: Lunges
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, step forward with right foot, and lower your body until right knee is at 90 degrees. Push back up to start. Repeat with the left leg.

exercises.name: Jump Squats
exercises.description: Perform a regular squat, but explode upwards when you push up. Land softly and repeat.

exercises.name: Glute Bridge
exercises.description: Lie on your back with knees bent, feet flat on the floor. Lift hips off the floor until knees, hips, and shoulders form a straight line. Hold for a few seconds, then lower back down.

exercises.name: Step-ups
exercises.description: Stand in front of a bench or step. Step up with your right foot, then left, then step down with right, then left. Repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Squat
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip. Lower your body into a deep squat, until your thighs are below parallel. Drive your heels into the ground to push yourself explosively back up to the start position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lunges
exercises.description: Stand tall with a dumbbell in each hand at arm's length by your sides. Take a step forward with your right foot and lower your body until your right knee is bent at least 90 degrees and your left knee nearly touches the floor. Push yourself back to the starting position and repeat with your left leg.

exercises.name: Stiff-Legged Deadlift
exercises.description: Hold a barbell in front of your body with your knees slightly bent. Slowly bend at your hip joint, not your waist, and lower the weight as far as possible without rounding your back, which should remain straight. Then return to the starting position.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Glute Bridge
exercises.description: Lie face up on the floor, with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. Lift your hips off the ground until your knees, hips and shoulders form a straight line. Squeeze those glutes hard and keep your abs drawn in so you don’t overextend your back during the exercise.

exercises.name: Barbell Front Squat
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Hold a barbell across your upper chest. You can either support the weight on your fingers, with wrists extended, or cross your arms to support the weight. Keeping your lower back arched, lower your body as deep as you can. Drive your heels into the floor to push yourself explosively back up to the start position.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Calf Raises
exercises.description: Stand up straight, then push through the balls of both feet to raise your body upward. Keep your abdominal muscles pulled in so that you move straight upward, not forward or backward.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Step-Ups
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand and stand in front of a bench or step that’s about knee height. Step up onto the bench with your right foot, pressing down while bringing your left foot up next to it. Step back with the left foot, returning to the floor, and bring down the right foot to complete one rep.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Squat Jumps
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Start by doing a regular squat, then engage your core and jump up explosively. When you land, lower your body back into the squat position to complete one rep. Land as quietly as possible, which requires control.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Squat
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, feet hip-width apart. Bend your knees and hips to lower your body as far as you can. Keep your heels flat on the floor. Drive back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lunges
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, feet hip-width apart. Step forward with one leg and lower your body until your front knee is at 90 degrees and your back knee is not touching the floor. Push back up to the starting position and switch legs.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, feet shoulder-width apart. Hinge at your hips and bend your knees while lowering your body until the dumbbells reach the middle of your shins. Keep your core tight and your back straight as you return to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Bulgarian Split Squat
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, one foot resting on a bench behind you. Lower your body until your front knee is at 90 degrees. Push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Single Leg Dumbbell Calf Raise
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in one hand, the other hand holding a support. Lift your heel as high as possible, then lower it below the level of the step.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Step Up
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, facing a bench. Step onto the bench with one foot, then push through that heel to lift your body onto the bench. Lower back down and repeat on the other side.

exercises.name: Barbell Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart and a barbell across your upper back. Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then push yourself back up to the start position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lunges
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand, step forward with one leg and lower your body until your front knee is bent at 90 degrees. Push back up to the start position and repeat with the other leg.

exercises.name: Barbell Deadlifts
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, knees slightly bent, and grasp a barbell with an overhand grip. Bend at your hips and knees and lower your torso until it's almost parallel to the floor. Pull the barbell to your upper abs. Pause, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Step-ups
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand and stand facing a bench. Place your right foot on the bench, push your body up until your right leg is straight and then return to the start position. Repeat with your left leg.

exercises.name: Barbell Front Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart and a barbell resting on your shoulders in front of your body. Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then push yourself back up to the start position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Goblet Squats
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell vertically in front of your chest, with both hands cupping the dumbbell. Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then push yourself back up to the start position.

exercises.name: Barbell Hip Thrusts
exercises.description: Sit on the ground with a barbell over your legs. Roll the bar so that it is directly above your hips, and lean back against a bench. Drive through your feet, extending your hips vertically through the bar. Then reverse the motion to bring the barbell back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Split Squats
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended at your sides. Stand in a staggered stance, one foot in front of the other. Bend your knees and lower your body as far in a lunge position. Push back up to starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Squats
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, under a barbell rack. Grab the barbell with an overhand grip, position it on your shoulders, and lift it off the rack. Lower your body by bending your knees until they are parallel to the floor. Push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Jump Squats
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Lower your body into a squat, then explode upwards, jumping as high as you can. Land softly and immediately lower into the next squat.

exercises.name: Barbell Lunges
exercises.description: Stand with a barbell across your upper back, then step forward with your right foot and sink into a lunge, so both legs are bent with your back knee as close to the floor as possible. Push off your front foot to return to the start. Do all the reps on one leg then swap.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Lunges
exercises.description: Stand tall with feet hip-width apart. Take a big step forward with right leg and start to shift weight forward so heel hits the floor first. Lower body until right thigh is parallel to the floor and right shin is vertical.

exercises.name: Barbell Deadlifts
exercises.description: Stand with your mid-foot under the barbell. Bend over and grab the bar with a shoulder-width grip. Bend your knees until your shins touch the bar. Lift your chest up and straighten your lower back. Take a deep breath, hold it, and stand up with the weight.

exercises.name: Glute Bridges
exercises.description: Lie on your back with your hands at your sides, knees bent, and feet flat on floor hip-width apart. Lift your hips off the floor until your knees, hips, and shoulders form a straight line. Hold your bridged position for a couple of seconds before easing back down.

exercises.name: Barbell Step-ups
exercises.description: Stand facing a bench. Hold a barbell across your upper back and step up onto the bench, but leave your trailing leg hanging off. Step back down and repeat, then do the full reps on one leg before switching to the other.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Calf Raises
exercises.description: Stand up straight, then push through the balls of both feet to raise your body upward. Keep your abdominal muscles pulled in so that you move straight upward, not forward or backward.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, holding medicine ball in front of you with both hands. Lower into a squat, keeping ball at chest level. Push back up, lifting ball above head in a smooth motion.

exercises.name: Battle Rope Waves
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, holding a battle rope in each hand. Lower into a half-squat position and alternate making waves with the rope as fast as possible.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Swings
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, holding a kettlebell in front of you with both hands. Lower into a half-squat position, then stand and swing the kettlebell up to chest level. Allow the kettlebell to fall back down, guiding it back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Squat
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart. Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor. Push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Jump Squats
exercises.description: Perform a bodyweight squat. As you rise back up, explode upwards and jump. Land softly and go right into the next squat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lunges
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand. Step forward with one foot and lower your body until your front knee is at 90 degrees. Push back up to the starting position and repeat with the other foot.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Step-ups
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand and stand in front of a bench or step. Step up onto the bench with one foot, then the other. Step down in reverse order.

exercises.name: Barbell Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, knees slightly bent. Hold a barbell with hands shoulder-width apart. Push your hips back and lower the barbell while keeping your back straight. Push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Front Squat
exercises.description: Hold a barbell at shoulder level, elbows pointing forward. Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor. Push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Single Leg Glute Bridge
exercises.description: Lie on your back with one foot flat on the floor and the other leg extended. Push your hips up off the floor as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Calf Raises
exercises.description: Stand on one foot. Push up onto your toes, raising your body upward. Keep your abdominal muscles pulled in so that you move straight upward, not forward or backward.

exercises.name: Barbell Squats
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Hold a barbell across your upper back with an overhand grip. Keeping your back straight, lower your body by bending your knees until your thighs are parallel with the floor. Push back up to the start.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lunges
exercises.description: Stand upright with a dumbbell in each hand at arm's length. Step forward with one leg and lower your body until your front knee is at 90 degrees and your back knee is just off the floor. Push back up to the start and switch legs.

exercises.name: Stiff-Legged Deadlifts
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell at arm's length in front of your thighs. Keeping your knees slightly bent and your back straight, bend at your hips and lower the barbell to ankle level. Push your hips forward to return to the start.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Step Ups
exercises.description: Stand in front of a bench holding a dumbbell in each hand. Place one foot on the bench, push down through your heel to lift your body up and step onto the bench. Return to the start position and repeat with the other leg.

exercises.name: Barbell Front Squats
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell at shoulder level in front of you. Keeping your back straight, lower your body by bending your knees until your thighs are parallel with the floor. Push back up to the start.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Split Squats
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand and one foot forward. Lower your body by bending your knees until your front knee is at 90 degrees and your back knee is just off the floor. Push back up to the start and switch legs.

exercises.name: Barbell Hip Thrusts
exercises.description: Sit on the ground with a barbell over your legs. Roll the barbell so that it is directly above your hips. Drive through your heels, extending your hips vertically through the bar. Your weight should be supported by your shoulder blades and your feet. Extend as far as possible, then reverse the motion to return to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Calf Raises
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms extended at your sides. Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your toes pointing straight ahead. Raise your heels off the ground and contract your calves. Slowly return to the starting position.

exercises.name: Jumping Squats
exercises.description: Start in a squat position. Jump explosively into the air, landing back into the squat position. Repeat.

exercises.name: Pistol Squats
exercises.description: Stand on one leg, with the other leg extended straight in front of you. Lower your body as far as you can, then push back up to the starting position. Repeat with the other leg.

exercises.name: Walking Lunges
exercises.description: Step forward with one foot and lower your body until your front knee is at a 90-degree angle. Push back up and repeat with the other leg.

exercises.name: Bulgarian Split Squats
exercises.description: Stand facing away from a bench. Extend one leg back and place the top of your foot on the bench. Lower your body until your front knee is at a 90-degree angle. Push back up and repeat with the other leg.

exercises.name: Barbell Overhead Press
exercises.description: Stand up straight with a barbell, palms facing forward. Press the weights overhead until your arms are completely straight. Slowly lower the weights back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raises
exercises.description: Stand straight, holding a dumbbell in each hand at arm's length. Keep your torso stationary and lift the dumbbells to your side with a slight bend on the elbow. Lower the weights back down slowly.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Shoulder Press
exercises.description: Stand straight with a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder level. Press the kettlebells upward until your arms are extended overhead. Lower them back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Upright Rows
exercises.description: Stand straight and hold a barbell in front of your body with palms facing you. Lift the barbell straight up to your collar bone level, keeping it close to your body. Lower it back down slowly.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Front Raises
exercises.description: Stand straight, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of your thighs. Lift the dumbbells straight in front of you until your arms are parallel to the floor. Lower them back down slowly.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Swings
exercises.description: Stand straight with a kettlebell between your legs. Bend at your hips and knees, swinging the kettlebell back between your legs. Quickly reverse the direction and drive your hips forward, swinging the kettlebell up to the chest level.

exercises.name: Barbell Shrugs
exercises.description: Stand straight, holding a barbell in front of your body with palms facing you. Shrug your shoulders as high as you can go, then lower them back down.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Reverse Flyes
exercises.description: Stand straight, holding a dumbbell in each hand, bend at the waist and let the arms hang down from the shoulders. Lift the dumbbells straight out to your sides until your arms are parallel to the floor. Lower them back down slowly.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Push-Ups
exercises.description: Get into a push-up position with one hand on a medicine ball. Lower your body towards the floor then push up explosively to switch the medicine ball to the other hand.

exercises.name: Barbell Military Press
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Hold a barbell at your shoulders, palms facing forward. Press the barbell overhead, extending your arms fully. Lower it back to your shoulders and repeat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand by your sides. Keeping your back straight, lift the weights out to the sides until they're at shoulder level. Lower them back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Upright Row
exercises.description: Hold a barbell in front of your body with your palms facing towards you. Pull the barbell up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. Lower it back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Slam
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a medicine ball. Lift it above your head and slam it into the ground in front of you as hard as you can. Pick it up and repeat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Front Raise
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of your thighs. Keeping your arms straight, lift the weights in front of you until they're at shoulder level. Lower them back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Shrug
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell in front of your thighs. Shrug your shoulders up towards your ears, then lower them back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Rotational Throw
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a medicine ball. Twist your torso to one side and then the other, throwing the ball against a wall. Catch it and repeat.

exercises.name: Pike Push ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position and walk your feet closer to your hands. Push your upper body down while keeping your lower body still, then push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Wall Walks
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position with your feet against a wall. Walk your feet up the wall while walking your hands closer to the wall. Walk back out to the starting position.

exercises.name: Handstand Push Ups
exercises.description: Start in a handstand position against a wall. Lower your body to the ground by bending your elbows, then push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Shoulder Tap
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Lift one hand to tap the opposite shoulder, then switch hands. Keep your core tight to maintain balance.

exercises.name: Decline Push Ups
exercises.description: Place your feet on a raised surface and your hands on the ground. Lower your body to the ground, then push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Inverted Rows
exercises.description: Hold onto a bar or straps with your body under the bar. Pull your chest to the bar, then lower back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dive Bomber Push Ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Lower your body down and forward, then push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Pull Ups
exercises.description: Grab a bar with your hands shoulder-width apart. Pull your body up until your chin is over the bar, then lower back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Overhead Press
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart. Hold a barbell in front of your neck, palms facing forward. Press the barbell straight up until your arms are fully extended. Lower back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart. Hold a dumbbell in each hand by your sides, palms facing inward. Raise the dumbbells out to the sides until they're shoulder level. Lower back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Upright Row
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart. Hold a barbell in front of your body with your hands just wider than shoulder-width apart. Pull the barbell up to your chest, keeping it close to your body. Lower back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Front Raise
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart. Hold a dumbbell in each hand in front of your thighs, palms facing your body. Raise the dumbbells in front of you until they're at shoulder level. Lower back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Shrug
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart. Hold a barbell in front of your thighs, palms facing your body. Shrug your shoulders up towards your ears. Lower back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Rear Delt Fly
exercises.description: Bend over at the waist with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. Raise the dumbbells out to the sides, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Lower back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Push Press
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart. Hold a barbell in front of your neck, palms facing forward. Bend your knees slightly, then push up and press the barbell straight up. Lower back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Arnold Press
exercises.description: Sit on a bench with a back support. Hold a dumbbell in each hand in front of your shoulders, palms facing your body. Press the dumbbells up while rotating your palms to face forward. Lower back down while rotating your palms to face your body. Repeat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended and by your side. Keep your back straight and lift the weights sideways until they're shoulder level, then slowly lower them.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Shoulder Press
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, at shoulder level with elbows bent. Push the weights up until your arms are fully extended above your head, then slowly lower them back to shoulder level.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Front Raise
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. Lift the weights in front of you at arm's length until they're shoulder level, then slowly lower them.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Upright Row
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended in front of your body and slightly less than shoulder width apart. Pull the weights straight up until your elbows form a 90-degree angle and the dumbbells are at chest level, then slowly lower them.

exercises.name: Pike Pushups
exercises.description: Start in a downward dog position with your hands and feet on the ground and your hips high in the air. Bend your elbows to lower your head towards the ground, then push back up.

exercises.name: Handstand Pushups
exercises.description: Kick up into a handstand against a wall. Bend your elbows to lower your head towards the ground, then push back up.

exercises.name: Shoulder Taps
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Lift one hand to tap your opposite shoulder, then switch sides.

exercises.name: Wall Walks
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position with your feet against a wall. Walk your hands towards the wall while walking your feet up the wall until you reach a handstand position, then walk back down.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Overhead Press
exercises.description: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and a dumbbell in each hand. Press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are completely straight. Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Kettlebell High Pull
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart and a kettlebell between your feet. Bend your knees, push your butt back, and grab the kettlebell with both hands. Stand up, lifting the kettlebell and pulling it toward your shoulder, keeping your elbows high.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Handstand Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a handstand position against a wall. Lower your body down until your head nearly touches the floor then push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand at arm's length. Keeping your back straight, lift the weights out to your side until they reach shoulder height. Lower them back down after a short pause.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Halo
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart holding a kettlebell by the horns close to your chest. Slowly circle the kettlebell around your head, making a halo.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Pike Push-up
exercises.description: Start in a pike position with your feet hip-width apart and your hands shoulder-width apart on the floor. Bend your elbows to lower your upper body towards the floor. Push back up to the start position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Front Raise
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand in front of your thighs. Keeping your torso stationary, lift the dumbbells in front of you with a slight bend on the elbows and the palms of the hands always facing down. Continue to go up until your arms are slightly above parallel to the floor. Lower the dumbbells back down slowly to the starting position.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Swing
exercises.description: Stand up straight, with feet a bit wider than hip-distance apart. Grab hold of the kettlebell with both hands, keeping the palms face down and arms in front of the body. Maintain a slight bend to the knee and drive the hips back, lowering the body and the kettlebell. Then, in a fluid motion, explosively drive the hips forward while swinging the kettlebell, keeping the glutes and core engaged.

exercises.name: Pike Pushups
exercises.description: Start in a pike position, with your feet hip-width apart and your hands shoulder-width apart. Lower your body until your head nearly touches the floor. Push your body back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Inverted Shoulder Press
exercises.description: Place your hands on the ground, walk your feet up a wall until your body is almost perpendicular to the floor. Lower your body to the floor by bending your elbows, then push yourself back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Handstand Hold
exercises.description: Kick up into a handstand against a wall and hold for time. Keep your body straight and tight, and your head in a neutral position.

exercises.name: Kettlebell push press
exercises.description: Hold a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder level. Bend your knees slightly and then push upward with your legs as you press the kettlebells directly overhead. Lower the kettlebells back to shoulder level and repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell high pull
exercises.description: Start with the kettlebell between your feet. Bend at the hips and knees and grab the kettlebell with one hand. Pull the kettlebell up to your shoulder, leading with your elbow, and then lower it back down under control.

exercises.name: Kettlebell swing
exercises.description: Hold a kettlebell with both hands and let it hang between your legs. Bend at the hips and knees and swing the kettlebell back between your legs and then forcefully swing it forward up to chest level. Let the kettlebell swing back between your legs and repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell snatch
exercises.description: Start with the kettlebell between your feet. Bend at the hips and knees and grab the kettlebell with one hand. In one motion, pull the kettlebell up to your shoulder and then overhead, ending with the kettlebell over your head and your arm straight. Lower the kettlebell back down under control.

exercises.name: Kettlebell clean and press
exercises.description: Start with the kettlebell between your feet. Bend at the hips and knees and grab the kettlebell with one hand. In one motion, pull the kettlebell up to your shoulder, flip your wrist so the kettlebell is resting on the outside of your forearm, and then press the kettlebell overhead. Lower the kettlebell back down under control.

exercises.name: Kettlebell bent over row
exercises.description: Stand with a kettlebell in each hand. Bend at the hips and knees and let the kettlebells hang at arm's length. Pull the kettlebells up to your ribs, pause, and then lower them back down under control.

exercises.name: Kettlebell front raise
exercises.description: Stand with a kettlebell in each hand at arm's length. Keeping your arms straight, lift the kettlebells in front of you until they're at shoulder level. Lower the kettlebells back down under control.

exercises.name: Kettlebell lateral raise
exercises.description: Stand with a kettlebell in each hand at your sides. Keeping your arms straight, lift the kettlebells out to the sides until they're at shoulder level. Lower the kettlebells back down under control.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Begin in a high plank position. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Push through your hands back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Slams
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Lift the medicine ball above your head, and slam it into the ground as hard as you can. Catch it on the bounce and repeat.

exercises.name: Pike Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a downward dog position with your hips high. Bend your elbows and lower your head towards the ground. Push back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Push Press
exercises.description: Hold a medicine ball at your chest with both hands. Push the ball up while extending your arms and then bring it back to your chest.

exercises.name: Barbell Overhead Press
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Hold a barbell at your shoulders with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Press the barbell directly overhead until your arms are fully extended. Lower the barbell back to your shoulders and repeat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. Keeping your back straight, lift your arms out to the sides until they're at shoulder height. Lower the dumbbells back to your sides and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Upright Row
exercises.description: Hold a barbell with your hands shoulder-width apart, palms facing your body. Pull the barbell up to your chin, keeping it close to your body. Lower it back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Front Raise
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of your thighs. Raise one dumbbell until your arm is parallel to the ground, then lower it back down. Repeat with the other arm.

exercises.name: Barbell Shrug
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell in front of your thighs with your hands shoulder-width apart. Shrug your shoulders up towards your ears, then lower them back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Reverse Fly
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Bend at your waist so your torso is nearly parallel to the ground, and let the dumbbells hang straight down. Keeping your back straight, lift your arms out to the sides until they're parallel to the ground. Lower the dumbbells and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Front Raise
exercises.description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with your hands shoulder-width apart in front of your thighs. Raise the barbell until your arms are parallel to the ground, then lower it back down and repeat.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Overhead Press
exercises.description: Sit on a bench with a backrest, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your shoulders. Press the dumbbells directly overhead until your arms are fully extended. Lower the dumbbells back to your shoulders and repeat.

exercises.name: Barbell Overhead Press
exercises.description: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, grab the barbell with an overhand grip, and press it overhead, extending arms fully. Lower the barbell back down to your chest.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raises
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand by your sides. Keep your back straight, then slowly lift the weights out to the side until they reach shoulder height. Lower them back down slowly.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Front Raises
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand at arm's length. Keep your torso stationary and lift the dumbbells in front of you with a slight bend on the elbow and the palms of the hands always facing down.

exercises.name: Barbell Upright Rows
exercises.description: Hold a barbell in front of your body with your palms facing towards you. Pull the barbell up towards your chin, keeping it close to your body.

exercises.name: Barbell Shrugs
exercises.description: Stand up straight with your feet at shoulder width as you hold a barbell with both hands in front of you using a pronated grip. Lift the barbell straight up by raising your shoulders and try to touch your ears with your shoulders.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Rear Delt Fly
exercises.description: Bend over at the waist with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. Raise both arms out to the sides as you squeeze your shoulder blades together. Lower the weights back down.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Keep your body straight and lower it to the floor by bending your arms. Push your body up back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Arnold Press
exercises.description: Sit and hold two dumbbells in front of you at upper chest level with your palms facing your body. As you press the dumbbells up, rotate your palms until they face forward. Pull them back to the starting position while rotating your palms back to the front.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Push back to the starting position. Make sure to keep your body in a straight line.

exercises.name: Pike push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a downward dog position with your feet hip-width apart. Bend your elbows and lower your head towards the ground. Push back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Shoulder taps
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Tap your left shoulder with your right hand and then your right shoulder with your left hand. Keep your core engaged and try not to rock your hips.

exercises.name: Arm circles
exercises.description: Stand tall with your arms extended by your sides. Make small circles with your arms in one direction, then switch to the other direction.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Shoulder Press
exercises.description: Stand or sit with a dumbbell in each hand at your shoulders, palms facing forward. Keep your back straight, brace your core, and then push up until your arms are fully extended above you. Lower them back after a short pause.

exercises.name: Barbell Upright Row
exercises.description: Grip a barbell with hands slightly less than shoulder-width apart. Pull the barbell directly upward until it is in line with your chin. Lower it back down to your waist after a short pause.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Pike Push Up
exercises.description: Start in a pike position with your feet hip-width apart and your hands shoulder-width apart. Bend your elbows and lower your upper body until the top of your head nearly touches the floor. Pause, and then push yourself back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand at your side. While keeping your back straight, lift the dumbbells up and out to the side until they reach shoulder level. Lower them back down after a short pause.

exercises.name: Barbell Front Raise
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell at the upper thighs with an overhand grip. Raise the barbell straight out in front of you until it is at shoulder level. Lower it back down after a short pause.

exercises.name: Tire Flips
exercises.description: Stand in front of a tractor tire, squat down, drive through your heels to lift and flip the tire.

exercises.name: Jump Through Tire
exercises.description: Jump in and out of the tire, increasing your heart rate for cardio.

exercises.name: Tire Push
exercises.description: Push the tire across a flat area for strength and conditioning.

exercises.name: Tire Slams
exercises.description: Lift the tire overhead and slam it down, engaging your core and upper body.

exercises.name: Incline Push-Ups
exercises.description: Use the tire as an incline for push-ups to work different muscles.

exercises.name: Tire Step-Ups
exercises.description: Step up onto the tire and back down to engage lower body muscles.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Swing
exercises.description: Start with a slight bend in your knees, holding a kettlebell between your legs with both hands. Drive your hips forward, swinging the kettlebell up to shoulder height. Let the kettlebell swing back between your legs as you bend your knees slightly. Repeat.

exercises.name: Push-Ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Push back up to the starting position. Repeat.

exercises.name: Kettlebell Squat
exercises.description: Hold a kettlebell by the handle in both hands at your chest. Squat down by bending at the knees and hips. Keep your chest up and back straight. Push back up to the starting position. Repeat.

exercises.name: Burpees
exercises.description: From a standing position, squat down and place your hands on the floor. Jump your feet back into a plank position. Jump your feet back in and stand up, jumping into the air and clapping your hands overhead. Repeat.

exercises.name: Push Ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Lower your body until your chest almost touches the floor. Push yourself back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart. Bend at the knees, pushing your hips back, until thighs are parallel with the floor. Push back up to starting position

exercises.name: Pull Ups
exercises.description: Grab the pull-up bar with your palms down. Pull yourself up until your chin is level with the bar. Lower yourself back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Lunges
exercises.description: Step forward with one leg, lowering your hips until both knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle. Step back to starting position. Repeat with other leg.

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
exercises.description: Sit on the edge of a chair or bench. Slide your butt off the surface, supporting yourself with your hands. Lower your body until your elbows form a 90-degree angle. Push back up to the start.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, toes pointing forward. Lower your body as far as you can by pushing your hips back and bending your knees. Pause, then slowly push yourself back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Get down on all fours, placing your hands slightly wider than your shoulders. Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor. Pause, then push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Rows
exercises.description: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. Bend forward at your hips and slightly bend your knees. Pull the dumbbells towards your chest, then lower them back down.

exercises.name: Lunges
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, take a step forward with right foot and lower your body until right knee is bent to 90 degrees. Push back up to the starting position and repeat with the left leg.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Deadlifts
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand in front of your thighs. Bend at your hips and knees, and lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor. Pause, then slowly rise back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Jumping Jacks
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart and hands at your sides. Simultaneously raise your arms out to the sides and jump your feet out to the sides. Immediately reverse the movement to jump back to the standing position.

exercises.name: Push-ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Place hands firmly on the ground, directly under shoulders. Lower your body. Push your body up.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart. Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the floor. Return to standing.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Deadlifts
exercises.description: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, feet hip-width apart. Hinge at your hips and knees, and lower your body until the dumbbells reach your ankles. Pause, then slowly rise back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on a flat bench holding a barbell in the rack above you with a shoulder-width, overhand grip. From the starting position, breathe in and lower the bar slowly until it skims the middle of your chest. Push the bar back to the starting position explosively as you breathe out.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Squat
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand at your sides and stand with your feet hip-width apart. Lower your body by bending your knees until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then push back up to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Deadlift
exercises.description: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of your thighs. Hinge at your hips and knees, lowering your torso until it's almost parallel to the floor. Push back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Bench Press
exercises.description: Lie on a bench holding a dumbbell in each hand at chest level. Push the weights straight up until your arms are fully extended, then lower them back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Row
exercises.description: Bend at your waist so your torso is almost parallel to the floor, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Pull the weights to your sides, squeeze your shoulder blades together, then lower them back down.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Overhead Press
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level, palms facing forward. Push the weights straight up until your arms are fully extended, then lower them back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Jumping Jacks
exercises.description: Stand upright with your legs together, arms at your sides. Bend your knees slightly, and jump into the air. As you jump, spread your legs to be about shoulder-width apart. Stretch your arms out and over your head. Jump back to starting position. Repeat.

exercises.name: Push-Ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Place hands firmly on the ground, directly under shoulders. Ground toes into the floor to stabilize your lower half. Begin to lower your body—keeping back flat and eyes focused about 3 feet in front of you to maintain a neutral neck—until chest grazes floor. Push back up. Repeat.

exercises.name: Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet a little wider than shoulder-width apart, hips stacked over knees, and knees over ankles. Extend arms out straight so they are parallel with the ground, palms facing down. Start to initiate the movement by inhaling and unlocking the hips, slightly bringing them back. Bend knees and lower body into a squat. Push back up to starting position. Repeat.

exercises.name: Lunges
exercises.description: Start by standing up tall. Step forward with one foot until your leg reaches a 90-degree angle. Your rear knee should remain parallel to the ground and your front knee shouldn’t go beyond your toes. Lift your front lunging leg to return to the starting position. Repeat with the other leg.

exercises.name: Jumping Jacks
exercises.description: Stand upright with your legs together, arms at your sides. Bend your knees slightly, and jump into the air. As you jump, spread your legs to be about shoulder-width apart. Stretch your arms out and over your head.

exercises.name: Push Ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Place hands firmly on the ground, directly under shoulders. Lower your body. Begin to lower your body—keeping your back flat and eyes focused about three feet in front of you to keep a neutral neck—until your chest grazes the floor.

exercises.name: Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet a little wider than shoulder-width apart, hips stacked over knees, and knees over ankles. Extend arms out straight so they are parallel with the ground, palms facing down. Goto a squat and exhale, then explode back up to standing, driving through heels.

exercises.name: Lunges
exercises.description: Stand upright, then step forward with one foot until your leg reaches a 90-degree angle. Your rear knee should remain parallel to the ground and your front knee shouldn’t go beyond your toes. Alternate legs with each repetition.

exercises.name: Burpees
exercises.description: From a standing position, drop into a squat with your hands on the ground just in front of your feet. Then kick your feet back behind you, keeping your arms extended so you are in a raised plank position. At this point, you can do a push up if you want, then bring your legs forward into a squat and leap up as high as you can.

exercises.name: Bodyweight Squats
exercises.description: Stand with feet hip-width apart, toes pointing forward. Bend your knees to lower your body as far as you can, keeping your shoulders back and chest up. Pause, then slowly push yourself back to the starting position.

exercises.name: Push Ups
exercises.description: Start in a high plank position. Bend your elbows and begin to lower your body down to the floor. When your chest grazes it, extend your elbows and return to the start. Focus on keeping your elbows close to your body during the movement.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lunges
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand, stand tall, and take a step forward with your right foot. Lower your body until your front knee is at a 90-degree angle. Push off your front foot to return to the starting position. Repeat with the other leg.

exercises.name: Dumbbell Rows
exercises.description: Hold a dumbbell in each hand and bend over at your waist. Keep your back flat and let your arms hang down. Pull the dumbbells towards your chest, then lower them back down.
